\begin{infobox}[Why no separate driver ICs?]
With only 4 digits and 7 segments (11 signal lines) plus 2 colon LEDs and 3 buttons, the entire interface fits comfortably within the ATmega328P-PU's 23 usable GPIO pins (Section~\ref{sec:pinout}), so no external display-driver or multiplexer IC was needed -- the microcontroller drives everything directly.
\end{infobox}

