\subsection{Why Prototype Before Going Standalone}
Before touching a bare chip, the complete display and button logic was built and tested on a breadboard \textbf{using a full Arduino Uno}. The goal of this phase was purely to validate software and wiring logic while iteration was still cheap:
\begin{itemize}
\item Correct segment-to-digit mapping (does "2" actually look like a 2 on every digit?)
\item Correct multiplexing refresh rate (no visible flicker, no ghosting between digits)
\item Correct button debounce and pull-up logic
\item Correct \texttt{millis()}-based timekeeping (no drift, no missed seconds)
\end{itemize}
Any mistake at this stage costs nothing more than a re-upload. The same mistake discovered after soldering the standalone chip costs a desoldering iron and a replacement part.

