\begin{infobox}[Persistence of Vision]
The human eye cannot distinguish individual flashes faster than roughly 50--60 times per second; it perceives them as continuously lit. By switching through all four digits well above this rate, the firmware shows only one physical digit at a time, yet the viewer perceives a steady, complete \texttt{14:35} on the display.
\end{infobox}

