\subsection{Why a Fresh Chip Needs a Bootloader}
A brand-new ATmega328P-PU from the factory has no Arduino bootloader and no fuse bits configured for a 16\,MHz external crystal -- it is generic silicon. Before it will accept sketches uploaded the "Arduino way," it must be burned with the Arduino Uno bootloader and have its clock-source fuses set correctly. A second Arduino Uno, reflashed to act as an \textbf{AVR ISP (In-System Programmer)}, performs this job -- no dedicated programmer hardware needs to be purchased.

